      %h2
        Q. How do I turn off word of the day push notifications?
      %p
        A. This method works for push notifications from any iOS application on an iPad,
        iPhone or iPod touch. Open the Settings app from the
        device&apos;s home screen. Tap Notifications on the master panel (iPad) or
        the main view of the Settings app (iPhone/iPod touch). Scroll down to see a
        list of apps &quot;In Notification Center.&quot; Tap the row for Dubsar.
        This will take you to a screen with a number of push-notification-related
        settings for Dubsar. Unfortunately, there is no master switch to turn off
        notifications altogether. You have to disable all the aspects independently
        on this screen. When you are done, it should look like this (the iPad view
        is similar):
      %h3 Dubsar with all notifications disabled
      = image_tag 'dubsar-notifications.png', alt: 'Dubsar Notifications', width: 300, height: 532, style: 'display: block;'
      %p
        When you have set the
        %em Notification Center, Badge App Icon, Sounds
        and
        %em View In Lock Screen
        switches to OFF and set the
        %em Alert Style
        to None, tap the back
        button in the navigation bar at the top, which says, &quot;Notifications.&quot;
        This will return you to the general Notifications settings. At the bottom, under
        Not In Notification Center, you&apos;ll see Dubsar:
      %h3 Dubsar no longer in Notification Center
      = image_tag 'notifications.png', alt: 'Dubsar not in Notification Center', width: 300, height: 532, style: 'display: block;'
      %p
        You can do the same for any application in the Notification Center. Of course,
        you can also fine-tune the settings for each application there, choosing which
        sort of notification, if any, you wish to receive, whether you want a badge on
        the app and whether it should play a sound when a notification arrives.
      %p
        If you originally said no when asked if the app could send push notifications
        but later change your mind, you can use the settings above to enable notifications
        from Dubsar. You can also do this after you&apos;ve removed Dubsar from the
        Notification Center, as described above.
     
